1557888.folder: 724 Columbus Avenue - West 95th Street, Manhattan, NY
1557888.title: 724 Columbus Avenue - West 95th Street

714865f-a.text:
March 29, 1969
West 95th St. N. side, looking N.E. toward Columbus Ave.
Note: 6 identical buildings:
Nos. 121-119-117-115-113-111
No. 115 in 1897 was occupied by
Dr. P.F. O'Hanlon, father of "Virginia
of the famous "Santa Claus' editorial.
N.Y. SUN Sept 21, 1897
No. 121 - Occupied in later years by Dr. O'Hanlon
No. 113 - occupied until 1918 by
Dr. Floyd Milford Crandall, Sec. of N.Y. County Medical Soc.,
Author of "How to Keep Well
(Doubleday - Page & Co. N.Y. 1903)
No. 111 - only house still occupied 1969
by Mrs. John Devlin
Above buildings are in West Side Urban Renewal Program
Photo fro H.A. Thomas
3805 Crescent St.
L.I. City N.Y. 11103

714866f-a.text:
141 to 137 West 95th Street, north side, between Columbus and Amsterdam Avenue's, showing at the left (no. 141) the house occupied by Willie Hoppe (worlds balkline billard champion) for the last 30 years and which has recently been sold.
May 9, 1938
George D. Chinn
NO REPRODUCTIONS
